<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97813483817326></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97813483817326><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97813483817326>RE: equip</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97813483817326#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Dec 30th 12:08 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It depends largely on how much you can spend.  You say lower, so I'm guessing not a lot.<br><br>Golded ear studs can be gotten from the cubert quest in Qeynos (+3 Int).  Anything +INT is good for a wiz.  Every lvl, each point of INT gets you a little more mana.<br><br>Raw silk armour is just about the best you can do before lvl 10 (unless you are hardcore twinked).  I sell for about 1pp per ac.<br><br>Take up tailoring, invest 21 practice points in it.  After making patchwork out of your ruined pelts, you can start making your own silk (much cheaper, and will make you money).<br><br>Robe, skip raw silk unless make it, or you can get it for less than 5pp.  Instead, get a Sr. Apprentice Robe.  +1 Mana, and the AC of silk.  It's about 5pp for my 75 Cha Wiz.  If you can shop in erudin, get it there.  The Erudin Sr is +2 mana (not alot, but every bit helps).  Just make sure you get the one for you class.  Wiz/Mag/Ecn are available, but will only fit 1 class.<br><br>Silver Jade rings give +5Hp/Mana, cost about 7pp a piece, I picked up a pair for 10p.<br><br>Try to get a runed totem staff ASAP (avg price, 20pp).  It's stats are good, and it's a decent weapon.  I carried one from 7 - 12.<br><br>Around 12, you'll get DD strong enough to be proud of.  Start looking for a Crysknife (??pp, mine was a gift) and a Skull of Jhen'Tra (20pp).  You're on your way to being a true, pure caster.<br><br><br>That's about all the advice I can give here, as I'm about 1 bub short of 13.  Live long fellow caster.<br><br><br>Iudar of Torvonnilous<br>Wizard of the 12th season<br><br><br>TIP:  East Commandlands (aka, The Great Marketplace), great place to buy anything.  I got most of my jewelery in that zone.  Try to get a TP or escort to freeport if your from the west coast.  You'll be glad you did.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
