	   <tr><td colspan=2>Agreed, <br><br>I&#8217;m a 35 level wizard on Bertoxx. I have 2 Serpentine Bracers for that very reason! A bit more AC and I dodge more often. I would recommend that every wizard try to get the AGI above 100.  However, I don&#8217;t recommend applying AGI from the start. AGI items are easy to find and most AGI item bonuses are very good like the bracers at +9 AGI. INT items are not so easy and they cost a lot to purchase to get so don&#8217;t go putting bonus point on AGI.<br><br>Dodging more and AC will give you that extra edge. My group seems to notice that I can take a few more hits as well. I&#8217;m not the typical wizard that dies off to fast. In fact, when a wizard is in a group it is best that you stand and take the hits so the group can help you. If you run around like a screaming little schoolgirl you will hinder the ability of the Warrior or Cleric to help.<br><br>Since I equipped the bracers I can regain &#8220;consciousness and continue casting&#8221; almost every time I get hit. It even happened after a double attack by a warrior. Hitting me for 20 &#8211;30 hp each time. I would say at least 50% - 70% more efficient then without AGI Bonuses.<br><br>BTW: I also have 186 intelligence! With the 2 Serpentine Bracers equipped!<br><br>Tuetatesu Ishwar<br>35th Wizard of the "AoS"<br><br><br>Tuetatesu Ishwar<br>35th Wizard of the "AoS"<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
