<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97628269029588></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97628269029588><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97628269029588>RE: Specialization?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97628269029588#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Dec 8th 1:38 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>In specialization, you must choose which one you want to get to lvl 50 first.  For wizards, Evocation is the one you should make sure that you get to lvl 50 first.  Because whatever one gets to that point first can continue up to the higher levels, I think it goes to a skill lvl of 200 or so.  Everything else stops at lvl 50.  If you screw up and get the wrong one to lvl 50 first there is a quest that can be done to reset your specializations.  Now for the reasons why:<br><br>Evocation is your direct damage and area damage spells, for a wizard, this is the most importiant sphere to worry about because DD spells are what we cast the most of.<br><br>The rest of the areas should be brought up to lvl 50 and not worried about.  From my understanding, specialization reduces mana use and time of casting.  There is one exception to this rule... Conjuration should not be worried about by a wizard until you get to higher levels.  We only get 2 or 3 spells that go into this area and all of them either take time to cast or use major mana.  So practice for our class in this one area is very difficult.  But you should not ignore this area because there is a spell that we get that is between lvls 50-60 that allows us to conjure a pet.  So we will need skill and specialization eventually in that sphere...<br><br>But remember, this only applies to wizards, every class has different needs.<br><br>Sincerely,<br>Alexandri Tigress (Erollsi Marr Server)<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
