<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97391734211319></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97391734211319><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97391734211319>RE: I think magicians should be nerfed, or wizards should be</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97391734211319#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 10th 11:35 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.72]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I am not a wizard, or a magician, I am a Shaman just doing some reading, so take this with a grain of salt =)<br><br>Wizards tend to feel they get shafted.  After all, that magician gets a pet and comparable damage at most levels....  And Damage shields, and and and...  But wizards &gt;do&lt; have some advantages.<br><br>#1)They get DD of three different types.  Ever been frustrated of nuking a mob with a cold spell and it is resistant to cold (just from Shaman experience here)?  So what do you do?  a) quit nuking and do something else b) Try to lower a resistance and go back to nuking c) switch DD types.  Wow, I would pick c myself if I had that option.  Wizards &gt;always&lt; have that option.  Mages have fire and magic based, but sometimes it is not wise to try the other type.  A lot of times their new big DD is a bolt type also, which can be hard to use in a dungeon.  Wizards have versatility within their DD.  <br><br>#2)Nothing says "mana dump" like a wizard. Here is some actual spell data :<br><br>Level 16 Magician Spell Shock of Flame<br>70 mana 97 max damage 2.75 cast time<br><br>Level 16 Wizard Spell Flame Shock <br>75 mana 110 max 2.5 cast time<br><br>Level 44 Magician Shock of Swords<br>250 mana 600 Max 6.1 cast time<br><br>Level 44 Wizard Conflaguration<br>250 mana 625 max 5.5 cast<br><br>Ok, both are similar in mana:damage ratio.  But notice the wizard spell is 90% of the casting time at 16 and 90% of the casting time at 44.  Granted, it is not much, but the wizard DOES cast faster, hence he can mana dump quicker, and burn that "oh crap KILL IT NOW" mob down quicker.  Once you add in the extra mana efficiency, and the reduced casting time, it does add up.<br><br>#3) After a certain level, wizards reduce the resistance % to their spells.  I have no hard data on this, but high level wizards spells are supposed to be resisted less than a similar spell cast by the same level person of another class.  A higher % of damage will get through more often.  Good stuff.<br><br>#4) Evac and travel spells.  Enough said.<br><br>#5) Wizards have some AWESOME AE spells.  If used properly, they can be EVIL.  But they do take practice to know when to use them.<br><br>I am not saying these 5 things are the only reason, or that they may be enough to convince you to keep playing you wizard.  But there are positives to the class.  Just trying to give you a pep talk =)  A well played Wizard is a truly awesome person to behold.  Nothing says lovin like double tapping something and watching it drop, and to only have the tank say, "Um, it was at 75% health..."  Yeah that is a little early to nuke hard, but sometimes you have to wow your groupmates =)<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>49 Shaman Bristlebane  <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
