	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 6th 9:16 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>This is true.  Actually, at level 34, the Magician's damage output with Cinder Bolt (336 max) edges out the Wizard's damage output with Ice Shock (320 max).  Both of these spells are the best direct damage for each class.  The only real diferences are the Wizard gets root, which the Magician never gets (his earth pet chain casts this spell however).  And, of course the Wizard gets ports, which are nice.  If you are looking for a vast diference in damagte output, you wont get that until level 49 with the Wizard's Ice Comet.  I would like to point out also, that the Wizard does not get any damage shield buffs, or the phantom armor series, which adds AC and regenerates hit points.  You have to decide what type of play will be best for you, and what is more important, teleports or buffs.  Hope this helps.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
