<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=97414853312477></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f97414853312477><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97414853312477>RE: Wizard question plz help!</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=97414853312477#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=1471><span id=Sage>Cryselle</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>35 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Nov 13th 3:48 PM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Frankly, you are never going to significanly outdamage a magician on a spell to spell basis until Ice Comet. You will cast them slightly faster, for slightly less mana, and slightly more damage. Surprisingly enough, it's not as raw a deal as it sounds even considering the other abilities Mages have. <br><br>At higher levels, speed and efficiency is /everything/, and us wizards have an edge in that. But more importantly, while a mage can solo more powerfully than we can, the more people added the more the wizard is the better class. If you go into a plane raid, or any other situation where there are multiple groups, magicians lose their Bolt spells, which are generally better than their shocks. Why is this? Because when there are 5 or 6 tanks beating on something, the magician can't get a clear line of sight for the bolt to go through. Also, pets are rarely allowed in Planes because of the fear of pathing problems. Meanwhile, us wizards are unhindered and nuke away gleefully.<br><br>So if soloing, or fighting as one of a pair or trilogy is your thing, magician is undoubtably more effective. If you live for the Raid, wizards rock. :)<br><br>Cryselle<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
